Title: 	dirutils

Description:
	Bash scripts for analysing directories

Author:
	Mark K Cowan, mark@battlesnake.co.uk

Requires:
	Bash, bc, awk, du, other things that come with a base installation

Descriptions:
	dirsize [ { -k | -m | -g } ] [ dirname ]
		Calculates the total size of files in <dirname> or the current
		directory, and outputs in bytes unless any of the size
		specifiers are given.
		
	dirstats [ dirname ]
		Prints a list of the 20 largest subdirectories in <dirname> or
		the current directory, ranked in descending order of size, with
		their corresponding sizes in the first column.  Does not follow
		symlinks or mounts to other file systems.
